{{Youmay|the negotiation ceremony|[[Jub Jub|the Ewok vocalization]]}}
The '''Jubjub''' was a business ceremony preceding an important negotiation. Food and entertainment were provided as a means of honoring the negotiation partner. The entertainment could include ritual combat between employees of both parties, upon which friendly wagers could be placed.

A Jubjub was declared by [[Gaar (title)|Gaar]] [[Suppoon]] before his talks with [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]]. The ceremony may have been traditional on Gaar's homeworld.

==Behind the scenes==
The word "Jubjub" appears in Lewis Carroll's poem [[Wikipedia:Jabberwocky|Jabberwocky]]: "Beware the Jubjub bird, and shun / The frumious Bandersnatch!" The similarly-spelled "Jub-Jub" is also the name of Selma's pet iguana on [[Wikipedia:The Simpsons|''The Simpsons'']].

